WEBVTT

00:02.335 --> 00:03.169
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"NECESSARY ROUGHNESS"...</i>

00:05.138 --> 00:06.039
Nico:
JESUS. HE BROUGHT A GUN?

00:06.072 --> 00:08.208
WHEN YOU'RE READY
TO REACH FOR THAT HAND,

00:08.241 --> 00:09.376
IT'S RIGHT HERE.

00:09.409 --> 00:10.510
RAY JAY?

00:10.543 --> 00:11.544
[ GASPS ]
OH, MY GOD.

00:11.578 --> 00:14.147
AM I NOT ENTITLED
TO SOME PRIVACY AROUND HERE?

00:14.180 --> 00:16.149
Ray Jr.: MOM!

00:16.182 --> 00:17.517
THAT WAS REALLY CLOSE.

00:17.550 --> 00:19.085
SNEAKING AROUND IS HOT.

00:19.119 --> 00:20.487
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:20.520 --> 00:23.323
Nico:
GABRIELLE IS FILING FOR DIVORCE.
SHE'S GOING AFTER THE HAWKS.

00:23.356 --> 00:24.357
YOU KNOW MARSHALL PITTMAN?

00:24.391 --> 00:26.493
Dani: YEAH, HE'S LIKE
AN ECCENTRIC MEGA MOGUL.

00:26.526 --> 00:29.496
OWNS NETWORKS, TEAMS,
INCLUDING THE NEW YORK HAWKS.

00:29.529 --> 00:32.198
MARSHALL?
NICO.

00:34.200 --> 00:38.204
Dani:
<i>WE TAKE PRECAUTIONS IN LIFE</i>
<i>TO KEEP US FROM HARM'S WAY...</i>

00:40.907 --> 00:45.512
<i>...KNEE PADS, HELMETS,</i>
<i>LIFE INSURANCE.</i>

00:45.545 --> 00:47.247
<i>BUT LET'S FACE IT.</i>

00:47.280 --> 00:50.383
<i>THERE'S ONLY SO MUCH WE CAN DO</i>
<i>TO PROTECT OURSELVES.</i>

00:55.188 --> 00:57.157
<i>NO MATTER HOW HARD WE TRY...</i>

00:57.190 --> 00:58.258
Announcer: HERE WE GO.

00:58.291 --> 01:00.260
NEW YORK DOLLS
AND GEORGIA BEE-ATCHES.

01:00.293 --> 01:03.163
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

01:03.196 --> 01:06.099
<i>...THERE'S NO SUCH THING</i>
<i>AS A PERFECT DEFENSE.</i>

01:07.200 --> 01:10.904
Announcer: LUCILLE BALLZ
IS COMING UP THE SIDE.

01:10.937 --> 01:11.838
OH! WHAT A HIT!

01:11.871 --> 01:15.575
TIPPER OVER
JUST CLOCKED LUCILLE BALLZ.

01:15.608 --> 01:18.111
[ GASPING, WHEEZING ]

01:21.414 --> 01:24.351
AND DisGrace KELLY IS DOWN.

01:24.384 --> 01:26.152
DID SHE GET HIT?

01:26.186 --> 01:29.322
WHAT THE HELL IS WRONG
WITH DisGrace KELLY?

01:29.356 --> 01:31.124
[ SOBS ]

01:36.429 --> 01:39.532
DALMORE SINGLE HIGHLAND MALT.

01:39.566 --> 01:41.234
MMM.

01:41.267 --> 01:42.268
[ CORK POPS ]

01:42.302 --> 01:44.371
IT'S A GIFT
FROM MARK CUBAN.

01:44.404 --> 01:47.774
WE WERE SPORT-FISHING
OFF THE COAST OF VENEZUELA.

01:47.807 --> 01:48.775
NONE FOR ME.

01:48.808 --> 01:50.577
IT'S A MUST!

01:50.610 --> 01:52.779
NOT LIKE THE SWILL
WE USED TO DRINK IN SINGAPORE.

01:52.812 --> 01:53.747
OH, IT DID THE JOB.

01:53.780 --> 01:57.217
WHEN HAVE EITHER OF US
EVER BEEN SATISFIED

01:57.250 --> 01:59.519
WITH THINGS
THAT JUST DID THE JOB?

01:59.552 --> 02:03.623
WE ARE BOTH AFFLICTED
WITH A TASTE FOR THE BEST.

02:03.656 --> 02:06.226
WHISKEY.

02:06.259 --> 02:08.328
TRAVEL.
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:08.361 --> 02:10.196
WOMEN.

02:10.230 --> 02:12.298
OKAY.

02:12.332 --> 02:14.334
IS THAT
WHAT YOU WANT TO TALK ABOUT?

02:14.367 --> 02:16.403
GABRIELLE?

02:16.436 --> 02:17.404
THEN LET'S TALK ABOUT IT.

02:17.437 --> 02:19.406
I DON'T WANT TO TALK.

02:19.439 --> 02:20.573
I WANT TO DRINK.

02:20.607 --> 02:22.575
THAT'S NOT WHY I'M HERE.

02:22.609 --> 02:24.577
THE QUESTION IS
WHY<i>YOU'RE</i>HERE.

02:24.611 --> 02:27.981
OTHER THAN TO EXACT
SOME SORT OF REVENGE.

02:28.014 --> 02:29.282
THAT'S THE THING
WITH EXQUISITE THOROUGHBREDS

02:29.315 --> 02:30.216
LIKE GABRIELLE.

02:30.250 --> 02:33.286
EVEN WHEN WE THINK
WE'RE ENOUGH FOR THEM,

02:33.319 --> 02:36.823
DEEP DOWN,
WE KNOW WE'RE NOT.

02:36.856 --> 02:38.992
I THOUGHT YOU DIDN'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

02:39.025 --> 02:40.694
GABRIELLE WILL DO
WHATEVER IT TAKES

02:40.727 --> 02:41.628
TO GET WHAT SHE WANTS.

02:41.661 --> 02:44.297
AND SHE WANTS
THE ONE THING IN THIS WORLD

02:44.330 --> 02:46.266
THAT MEANS MORE TO ME
THAN MONEY --

02:46.299 --> 02:51.004
<i>MY</i>TEAM,
THE NEW YORK HAWKS.

02:51.037 --> 02:54.240
WELL, I WILL PROTECT THIS TEAM
BY ANY MEANS NECESSARY.

02:54.274 --> 02:56.209
THAT'S WHERE<i>YOU</i>COME IN.

03:00.280 --> 03:01.281
ARE YOU WITH ME?

03:05.452 --> 03:07.487
OLD FRIEND.

03:12.892 --> 03:15.261
WHY?
JUST GIVE ME A REASON.

03:15.295 --> 03:17.330
REALLY? 'CAUSE I GAVE YOU
ABOUT 10.

03:17.364 --> 03:20.700
OKAY, YOU'RE NOT GONNA BE ALONE
IN THIS HOUSE WITH OLIVIA.

03:20.734 --> 03:22.869
'CAUSE YOU DON'T WANT US
TO DO IT HERE.

03:22.902 --> 03:24.337
YOU MEAN "DO IT<i>AGAIN,"</i>
DON'T YOU?

03:24.371 --> 03:25.705
WHEN YOU'RE
SUPPOSED TO BE STUDYING?

03:25.739 --> 03:27.607
RAY JAY,
SHE TOOK ADVANTAGE OF YOU.

03:27.640 --> 03:31.378
SHE VIOLATED THE...
TUTOR/TUTEE RELATIONSHIP.

03:31.411 --> 03:34.347
YOU--
YOU JUST MADE THAT UP!

03:34.381 --> 03:36.750
NO, IT GOES WAY BACK
TO THE ANCIENT GREEKS.

03:36.783 --> 03:38.051
SO LOOK IT UP --

03:38.084 --> 03:40.053
WHILE YOU'RE STUDYING
BY YOURSELF.

03:40.086 --> 03:41.654
YOU KNOW, DAD THINKS
YOU'RE OVERREACTING.

03:41.688 --> 03:42.722
OH, REALLY?

03:42.756 --> 03:44.491
'CAUSE THIS IS<i>MY</i>HOUSE,
<i>MY</i>RULES,

03:44.524 --> 03:45.759
SO WHILE
YOU'RE LIVING HERE,

03:45.792 --> 03:47.660
YOU'RE GONNA
RESPECT THOSE RULES.

03:47.694 --> 03:48.728
UNDERSTAND EACH OTHER?

03:48.762 --> 03:52.332
YEAH.
LOUD AND CLEAR.

03:52.365 --> 03:53.767
AND RIDICULOUS!

03:53.800 --> 03:55.902
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

03:55.935 --> 03:57.904
[ SIGHS ]

03:57.937 --> 04:00.473
<i>YOU'RE</i>ON MY SIDE, AREN'T YOU?

04:02.942 --> 04:06.446
YO! I TALKED TO YOUR DOORMAN.
I KNOW YOU'RE HERE.

04:06.479 --> 04:08.448
[ HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING LOUDLY ]

04:08.481 --> 04:10.917
ALL RIGHT, T. LET'S CUT
THE BULLSHIT, ALL RIGHT?

04:10.950 --> 04:12.786
YOU'VE SKIPPED
TWO TRAINING SESSIONS,

04:12.819 --> 04:13.787
TWO THERAPY SESSIONS,

04:13.820 --> 04:16.356
AND I AM NOT LEAVING
UNTIL YOU OPEN THE DOOR.

04:16.389 --> 04:17.791
I'VE GOT ALL DAY.

04:17.824 --> 04:20.460
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

04:37.644 --> 04:39.112
COME IN?
MAY AS WELL.

04:39.145 --> 04:40.780
I AIN'T GOING OUT THERE.

04:43.783 --> 04:45.452
THAT'S YOU?

04:45.485 --> 04:46.720
DisGrace KELLY?

04:46.753 --> 04:48.822
I KNOW -- IT SOUNDS LIKE
A TATTED-OUT CHICK

04:48.855 --> 04:50.490
WITH PINK HAIR OR SOMETHING,
RIGHT?

04:50.523 --> 04:52.792
EVERYONE IN DERBY
HAS AN ALTER EGO.

04:52.826 --> 04:54.461
IT'S LIKE THE MEANEST,
TOUGHEST PART OF YOURSELF

04:54.494 --> 04:56.396
IS WHAT YOU PUT
ON THE TRACK AT NIGHT.

04:56.429 --> 04:58.465
AND WHAT ABOUT
DURING THE DAY?

04:58.498 --> 05:00.500
I'M, UH,
GRACE DENISE CHARLESTON,

05:00.533 --> 05:02.435
MANAGER
AT A SOFTWARE FIRM.

05:02.469 --> 05:03.770
BUT DERBY'S
WHERE MY HEART IS.

05:03.803 --> 05:06.406
THOSE GIRLS
ARE LIKE FAMILY TO ME.

05:06.439 --> 05:07.841
WHAT ABOUT
YOUR<i>REAL</i>FAMILY?

05:07.874 --> 05:08.775
BOSTON -- SUBURBS.

05:08.808 --> 05:11.811
MY DAD'S A LAWYER.
MOM'S A FULL-TIME DRUNK.

05:11.845 --> 05:13.813
MY BROTHER'S
A PSYCHO FRAT BOY,

05:13.847 --> 05:15.815
AND MY SISTER'S
IN A WHEELCHAIR.

05:15.849 --> 05:18.818
WE'RE LIKE THE ROYAL TENENBAUMS,
MINUS THE "ROYAL" PART.

05:18.852 --> 05:21.421
TELL ME WHY YOU'RE HERE
TODAY, GRACE.

05:21.454 --> 05:24.758
LIKE I SAID
ON THE PHONE...

05:24.791 --> 05:28.695
SOMETHING WEIRD HAPPENED
DURING LAST WEEK'S BOUT.

05:28.728 --> 05:31.831
UH, IT WAS AN ODOR
THAT MADE YOU COLLAPSE?

05:32.766 --> 05:35.769
THE TEAM OWNER RAN TESTS.
THEY FOUND NOTHING.

05:35.802 --> 05:38.738
NO CHEMICALS,
NO TOXIC SUBSTANCES.

05:38.772 --> 05:41.741
AND ANYBODY ELSE
HAVE THAT REACTION?

05:41.775 --> 05:42.876
SMELL ANYTHING?

05:42.909 --> 05:44.377
NO.

05:45.478 --> 05:48.848
LOOK...
I'M THE TEAM CAPTAIN.

05:48.882 --> 05:52.752
AND NEXT WEEK, WE'RE PLAYING
FOR NATIONAL CHAMPIONSHIPS.

05:52.786 --> 05:55.889
THE TEAM OWNER, NITRO,
WON'T LET ME BACK ON THE TRACK

05:55.922 --> 05:57.857
UNTIL MY HEAD
IS STRAIGHT.

05:57.891 --> 06:02.195
WHEN I COLLAPSED, I TOOK
OTHER SKATERS DOWN WITH ME.

06:02.228 --> 06:03.263
MM.

06:03.296 --> 06:07.500
EVERYONE KEEPS SAYING
THAT THE SMELL WAS IN MY HEAD.

06:07.534 --> 06:09.769
BUT HOW CAN I SMELL SOMETHING
IF IT'S NOT EVEN THERE?

06:11.805 --> 06:13.673
SO, HOW BAD IS HE?

06:13.707 --> 06:15.675
THINK HOWARD HUGHES,
MINUS THE FINGERNAILS.

06:15.709 --> 06:16.843
WON'T COME
OUT OF HIS APARTMENT.

06:16.876 --> 06:18.678
NOT EVEN FOR THERAPY.

06:18.712 --> 06:20.480
SO, LAST WEEK,
HE NEARLY GOES "DIRTY HARRY"

06:20.513 --> 06:21.348
AT A FAN CONVENTION.

06:21.381 --> 06:22.849
THIS WEEK,
HE'S GOT A DEBILITATING CASE

06:22.882 --> 06:24.684
OF "LOCK ME UP
AND THROW AWAY THE KEY"?

06:24.718 --> 06:26.686
THE GUY TOOK TWO BULLETS
EIGHT WEEKS AGO.

06:26.720 --> 06:29.222
WE CAN'T BLAME HIM FOR WANTING
TO LAY LOW A LITTLE BIT.

06:29.255 --> 06:31.791
IT'S AGORAPHOBIA --
CLASSIC SYMPTOM OF PTSD.

06:31.825 --> 06:33.526
WE HAVE TO BE PATIENT.

06:33.560 --> 06:34.894
PTSD, MY ASS.

06:34.928 --> 06:36.796
THE DEADLINE
FOR PULLING THE TRIGGER

06:36.830 --> 06:38.665
ON HIS ROSTER BONUS
IS NEXT WEEK.

06:38.698 --> 06:39.733
THAT'S $7 MILLION
TO A PLAYER

06:39.766 --> 06:41.768
WHO<i>WAS</i>THE FOCAL POINT
OF OUR OFFENSE.

06:41.801 --> 06:42.702
AND RIGHT NOW
WE HAVE NO IDEA

06:42.736 --> 06:44.838
IF THE MAN CAN EVEN RUN
A 40-YARD DASH!

06:44.871 --> 06:46.539
I'LL GET HIM THERE.

06:46.573 --> 06:47.707
[ SIGHS ]

06:47.741 --> 06:49.709
I BETTER BREAK THE NEWS
TO THE G.M.

06:49.743 --> 06:52.579
DON'T BOTHER. I JUST TOOK HIM
OUT BACK AND SHOT HIM.

06:54.848 --> 06:56.683
AS OF 11:15
THIS MORNING,

06:56.716 --> 06:59.519
CURTIS PIERCE, GENERAL MANAGER
OF THE NEW YORK HAWKS,

06:59.552 --> 07:00.854
WAS RELIEVED
OF HIS DUTIES.

07:02.589 --> 07:05.091
HELLO, COACH!

07:05.125 --> 07:06.826
DONNALLY.
[ CHUCKLES ] SIR.

07:06.860 --> 07:09.496
AND YOU MUST BE
THE HEAD-SHRINKER.

07:09.529 --> 07:11.531
YOU MUST BE...

07:11.564 --> 07:15.268
MARSHALL PITTMAN,
OWNER OF THE NEW YORK HAWKS.

07:15.301 --> 07:17.871
<i>AND,</i>AS OF 11:16
THIS MORNING,

07:17.904 --> 07:20.874
THE NEW GENERAL MANAGER.

07:21.941 --> 07:25.812
LET'S GO FIND MY OFFICE,
SHALL WE?

07:25.845 --> 07:39.592
* BABY, WORK YOUR MAGIC ON ME

07:39.626 --> 07:40.860
Pittman: TRASH IT.

07:40.894 --> 07:42.629
Pat: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS
WANT TO DISCUSS

07:42.662 --> 07:43.697
YOU NAMING YOURSELF G.M.

07:43.730 --> 07:45.231
NOTHING TO DISCUSS.

07:45.265 --> 07:46.733
DECISION'S BEEN MADE.

07:46.766 --> 07:49.836
NOW, WHEN CAN I SEE
TERRENCE KING RUN?

07:49.869 --> 07:52.772
Matthew:
WELL, THE PLAYERS HAVEN'T EVEN
OFFICIALLY REPORTED YET.

07:52.806 --> 07:54.674
AND TERRENCE JUST STARTED
HIS REHAB.

07:54.708 --> 07:56.676
HE'S STILL RECUPERATING
FROM THE SHOOTING.

07:56.710 --> 07:58.812
YEAH, BUT T.K.'s GOT
A BIG BONUS PENDING.

07:58.845 --> 08:00.180
I GOT TO PULL THE TRIGGER.

08:00.213 --> 08:01.614
LOOK, MR. PITTMAN,

08:01.648 --> 08:03.850
UM, OBVIOUSLY, YOU WANT
YOUR STAR WIDE RECEIVER

08:03.883 --> 08:06.619
TO BE IN TOP PHYSICAL
AND EMOTIONAL CONDITION.

08:06.653 --> 08:07.854
AND WE CAN GET HIM THERE.

08:07.887 --> 08:09.189
IT'S JUST GONNA TAKE
A LITTLE TIME.

08:09.222 --> 08:10.857
TIME, DONNALLY,

08:10.890 --> 08:13.893
IS THE ONE COMMODITY
I CAN'T AFFORD.

08:13.927 --> 08:17.597
I EITHER HAVE TO PAY
TERRENCE KING $7 MILLION

08:17.630 --> 08:19.199
BY THE END OF NEXT WEEK

08:19.232 --> 08:21.768
OR CUT HIM FROM MY ROSTER.

08:21.801 --> 08:23.770
[ Chuckling ]
LOOK, I'M NOT UNREASONABLE.

08:23.803 --> 08:26.773
I'M NOT SUGGESTING
YOU RUN HIM<i>TOMORROW.</i>

08:26.806 --> 08:28.675
FRIDAY'S FINE.

08:29.809 --> 08:31.244
Matthew:
IT'S CRAZY, NICO.

08:31.277 --> 08:32.379
WELL,
IT'S NOT YOUR $7 MILLION.

08:32.412 --> 08:35.782
LOOK, IF PITTMAN WANTS TO TALK
TO T.K.'s DOCTORS, FINE,

08:35.815 --> 08:37.650
BUT DON'T PUT HIM
OUT ON THE FIELD

08:37.684 --> 08:38.718
WHEN HE'S NOT READY,
OKAY?

08:38.752 --> 08:41.621
THE PRESSURE OF A TRYOUT,
IN HIS STATE OF MIND --

08:41.654 --> 08:42.856
IT'S A RECIPE
FOR DISASTER.

08:42.889 --> 08:44.891
WE CAN'T EVEN GET T.K.
OUT OF HIS APARTMENT,

08:44.924 --> 08:46.659
LET ALONE OUT HERE.

08:46.693 --> 08:48.695
CONSIDER THAT...
HANDLED.
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

08:48.728 --> 08:51.264
[ SIGHS ] WHY DON'T I LIKE
THE SOUND OF THAT?

08:51.297 --> 08:53.299
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

08:57.671 --> 08:59.272
GIVE ME ONE GOOD REASON
I SHOULD LEAVE THIS APARTMENT.

08:59.305 --> 09:01.808
I'LL GIVE YOU 7 MILLION --
YOUR BONUS.

09:01.841 --> 09:03.777
I DON'T FEEL SAFE.

09:03.810 --> 09:04.844
I'M GONNA GET YOU
PROTECTION.

09:04.878 --> 09:07.247
I GOT PROTECTION.
I DON'T NEED THAT. I GOT PEEPS.

09:07.280 --> 09:09.716
I'M TALKING ABOUT DISCREET
AND PROFESSIONAL PROTECTION --

09:09.749 --> 09:12.719
PEOPLE THAT CAN WATCH YOU
24 HOURS A DAY, 7 DAYS A WEEK.

09:12.752 --> 09:13.887
THEY DO WINDOWS,
TOO?

09:13.920 --> 09:16.923
HA HA HA.
THAT'S SO FUNNY.

09:18.758 --> 09:19.726
THIS.

09:19.759 --> 09:20.827
COOKIES?

09:20.860 --> 09:22.262
YES OR NO, TERRENCE?

09:22.295 --> 09:23.663
ON THE PROTECTION.

09:25.932 --> 09:27.801
SO GIVE ME
THE REST OF THEM.

09:29.936 --> 09:31.705
COME ON. LET'S GO.

09:31.738 --> 09:33.673
HAND THEM OVER --
ALL OF THEM.

09:36.343 --> 09:37.344
OKAY.

09:42.916 --> 09:43.883
WHAT THE...

09:43.917 --> 09:46.953
AND WHATEVER
YOU'RE SITTING ON.

09:46.986 --> 09:49.789
COME ON. IT'S NOT
MY FIRST RODEO. LET'S GO.

09:49.823 --> 09:51.825
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]
DAMN.

09:53.793 --> 09:55.862
OH. OKAY. NICE.

09:55.895 --> 09:57.664
I GUESS YOU FIGURE

09:57.697 --> 09:58.898
IF THE GLOCK DOESN'T STOP THEM,
THE NUNCHUCKS WILL?

09:58.932 --> 10:00.834
WORKED FOR BRUCE LEE.

10:00.867 --> 10:01.901
HAPPY NOW?

10:01.935 --> 10:04.337
I WILL BE
WHEN I FIND OUT

10:04.371 --> 10:06.806
WHO GIVES YOU ILLEGAL
AND UNLICENSED FIREARMS.

10:06.840 --> 10:09.743
SERIAL NUMBERS SCRATCHED OFF --
KIND OF A GIVEAWAY.

10:10.910 --> 10:11.911
YOU KNOW,
AFTER HAPPY HOUR,

10:11.945 --> 10:14.748
IF YOU LOOK STRAIGHT ACROSS,
YOU CAN SEE BOSOMS.

10:14.781 --> 10:16.816
I'LL CONNECT THE DOTS
ON MY OWN.

10:18.184 --> 10:21.855
DIRK AND CONRAD --
YOUR NEW BABYSITTERS.

10:21.888 --> 10:24.891
PLEASE -- GET DRESSED.

10:24.924 --> 10:26.926
MR. KING.

10:32.932 --> 10:34.934
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

10:40.940 --> 10:42.709
OH, MY GOD!

10:42.742 --> 10:44.878
IS THE POINT OF THE GAME
TO KILL EACH OTHER?

10:44.911 --> 10:46.479
[ LAUGHS ]
SEEMS LIKE IT, RIGHT?
YEAH.

10:46.513 --> 10:47.914
THERE'S TWO TEAMS OF FIVE
ON THE TRACK, OKAY?

10:47.947 --> 10:49.816
AND THERE'S FOUR BLOCKERS
AND A JAMMER --

10:49.849 --> 10:51.718
OUR VERSION
OF THE RUNNING BACK.

10:51.751 --> 10:54.788
THE JAMMER'S JOB IS TO GET
THROUGH THE OPPOSING BLOCKERS,

10:54.821 --> 10:57.057
AND FOR EVERY SKATER
SHE PASSES, SHE GETS A POINT.

10:57.090 --> 10:59.859
THE BIGGEST RULE IN DERBY --
DON'T BE A DOUCHE.

10:59.893 --> 11:01.928
OH, THAT'S FUNNY, 'CAUSE
THAT'S A RULE IN<i>MY</i>LIFE, TOO.

11:01.961 --> 11:03.430
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:03.463 --> 11:05.932
OH, NITRO GLITTERIN',
THIS IS, UH, DR. SANTINO.

11:05.965 --> 11:07.767
NITRO'S OUR TEAM OWNER.

11:07.801 --> 11:09.903
PLEASURE.
YOU EVER BEEN?
HMM?

11:09.936 --> 11:12.806
TO A DERBY BOUT.
NO, I HAVEN'T.

11:12.839 --> 11:14.040
FASTEST-GROWING WOMEN'S SPORT
IN AMERICA.

11:14.074 --> 11:15.809
Lucille: DisGrace!

11:15.842 --> 11:17.844
[ LUCILLE AND GRACE SHRIEK ]

11:17.877 --> 11:19.879
WHEN YOU COMING BACK,
BITCH?

11:19.913 --> 11:21.481
I'M WORKING ON IT.

11:21.514 --> 11:23.950
THIS IS LUCILLE BALLZ.
DR. SANTINO.

11:23.983 --> 11:25.852
HI.
HELLO.

11:25.885 --> 11:27.921
ALL RIGHT, GET HER
FIXED IN THE HEAD REAL SOON,

11:27.954 --> 11:29.823
'CAUSE WE CAN'T WIN
WITHOUT HER.

11:29.856 --> 11:31.758
I'LL SEE YOU NEXT WEEK
AT THE CHAMPS.

11:31.791 --> 11:34.894
LISTEN, I'VE GOT EXECS COMING IN
FROM TWO SPORTS NETWORKS

11:34.928 --> 11:36.963
TO SEE THE CHAMPS BOUT
NEXT WEEK,

11:36.996 --> 11:39.766
AND THERE'S A $2 MILLION
TV CONTRACT RIDING ON THIS.

11:39.799 --> 11:42.902
I TOLD GRACE -- WHATEVER IT
TAKES TO GET HER BACK ON TRACK

11:42.936 --> 11:44.904
AND BACK ON<i>MY</i>TRACK,
THAT'S FINE.

11:44.938 --> 11:47.907
BUT I GOT TO KNOW
THIS ISN'T GONNA HAPPEN AGAIN.

11:47.941 --> 11:49.943
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

11:49.976 --> 11:52.045
TEAM MEETING IN THE LOCKER ROOM!
LET'S GO!

11:52.078 --> 11:54.080
Dani: SO,
WE'RE TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

11:54.114 --> 11:56.783
WHAT TRIGGERED THE EPISODE
THAT YOU HAD.

11:56.816 --> 11:58.985
SOMETIMES, REVISITING THE SCENE
BRINGS UP DETAILS

11:59.019 --> 12:00.954
THAT THE PERSON
MAY HAVE REPRESSED.

12:00.987 --> 12:02.956
GO BACK TO THAT NIGHT.

12:02.989 --> 12:05.859
YOU JUST TAKE ME
THROUGH WHAT HAPPENED.

12:07.894 --> 12:08.762
OKAY.

12:08.795 --> 12:13.066
UM...IT WAS THE FIRST JAM
OF THE BOUT.

12:13.099 --> 12:15.869
AND WE ALL LINED UP,
AS USUAL.

12:15.902 --> 12:19.005
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]
<i>THE JAM STARTED.</i>

12:19.039 --> 12:20.040
<i>EVERYTHING SEEMED NORMAL.</i>

12:20.073 --> 12:22.008
<i>I WAS LUCI'S BLOCKER,</i>

12:22.042 --> 12:25.011
<i>I WENT UP AHEAD</i>
<i>TO CLEAR A PATH FOR HER.</i>

12:25.045 --> 12:28.515
AND THAT'S
WHEN TIPPER NAILED HER --

12:28.548 --> 12:30.817
<i>A BLOCKER FOR THE OTHER TEAM.</i>

12:30.850 --> 12:34.020
<i>SHE HIT LUCI SO HARD,</i>
<i>SHE SKIDDED HER OFF THE TRACK.</i>

12:36.022 --> 12:37.123
<i>I COULDN'T SEE HER.</i>

12:37.157 --> 12:38.591
<i>COULDN'T SEE LUCI?</i>

12:38.625 --> 12:39.659
<i>I STARTED TO PANIC.</i>

12:39.693 --> 12:42.028
BECAUSE I DIDN'T --
I DIDN'T KNOW WHERE SHE WAS.

12:42.062 --> 12:43.997
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO HER.

12:44.030 --> 12:47.534
AND THEN FROM NOWHERE
WAS THIS -- THIS SMELL --

12:47.567 --> 12:50.870
<i>OVERWHELMING, TOXIC FUMES.</i>

12:50.904 --> 12:52.939
<i>I-I CAN'T BREATHE.</i>

12:52.972 --> 12:54.007
I COLLAPSED.

13:02.649 --> 13:05.585
[ Voice breaking ] WHAT HAPPENED
TO ME, DR. SANTINO?

13:05.618 --> 13:08.054
I'M NOT QUITE SURE YET.

13:08.088 --> 13:11.825
BUT WE ARE
GOING TO FIGURE IT OUT.

13:15.895 --> 13:17.931
RAY JAY, STOP.

13:17.964 --> 13:19.599
WHAT? WE TOO CLOSE
TO YOUR HOUSE?

13:19.632 --> 13:20.900
I CAN MOVE THE CAR.

13:20.934 --> 13:23.036
COME ON.
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

13:23.069 --> 13:25.972
I MEAN, DOING IT IN A CAR?
IT'S SO HIGH SCHOOL.

13:26.006 --> 13:28.908
YEAH,
BUT WE'RE<i>IN</i>HIGH SCHOOL.

13:30.010 --> 13:32.045
OKAY. MAYBE WE CAN
GO TO YOUR HOUSE.

13:32.078 --> 13:33.947
YEAH, OR MAYBE
YOU SHOULD TELL YOUR MOM

13:33.980 --> 13:35.115
TO STOP TREATING US
LIKE CHILDREN.

13:37.050 --> 13:37.984
I MEAN, COME ON.

13:38.018 --> 13:39.986
LIKE SHE WASN'T DOING IT
WHEN SHE WAS OUR AGE?

13:40.020 --> 13:41.588
OH, NO, NO, NO, NO.

13:41.621 --> 13:44.090
[ LAUGHS ]
NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

13:44.124 --> 13:47.994
I WILL NOT BE BANNED
FROM MY BOYFRIEND'S HOUSE,

13:48.028 --> 13:49.996
NO MATTER HOW HOT HE IS.

13:50.030 --> 13:51.998
OKAY,
SO, WHAT DO YOU WANT

13:52.032 --> 13:54.934
YOUR HOT BOYFRIEND
TO DO ABOUT IT?

13:58.972 --> 14:01.641
I WANT YOU
TO STICK UP FOR US.

14:01.675 --> 14:04.577
I'M NOT INTERESTED
IN DATING A BOY, RAY JAY.

14:04.611 --> 14:06.946
I'M INTERESTED
IN DATING A<i>MAN.</i>

14:17.157 --> 14:20.026
MM...HMM.

14:20.060 --> 14:23.029
NO, NO, THE KIDS ARE GONE
FOR THE NIGHT.

14:24.164 --> 14:28.601
MATT, HOW FAR AWAY ARE YOU?

14:28.635 --> 14:29.669
OKAY, GOOD.

14:29.703 --> 14:31.104
YEAH, I CAN'T WAIT.

14:31.137 --> 14:34.007
HMM?

14:34.040 --> 14:35.041
I'M A LITTLE DISTRACTED,

14:35.075 --> 14:37.644
[ Chuckling ] BUT I WON'T BE
WHEN YOU GET HERE.

14:37.677 --> 14:39.045
[ LAUGHS ]

14:39.079 --> 14:40.914
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

14:43.049 --> 14:45.151
YOU LITTLE TEASE!

14:45.185 --> 14:48.955
WERE YOU HERE THE WHOLE TIME,
SITTING IN THE DRIVEWAY?

14:51.624 --> 14:53.660
IS THIS A BAD TIME?

14:59.065 --> 15:06.506
I got to take
a rain check.

15:06.539 --> 15:09.576
SO...

15:09.609 --> 15:12.579
THIS IS
WHERE THE MAGIC HAPPENS.

15:12.612 --> 15:15.315
I TAKE IT THAT
YOU'VE NEVER BEEN IN THERAPY.

15:15.348 --> 15:17.417
ASIDE FROM SOME ILL-FATED
MARRIAGE COUNSELING,

15:17.450 --> 15:20.520
I AM A THERAPY VIRGIN.

15:20.553 --> 15:23.289
BUT...
I'M GAME IF<i>YOU</i>ARE.

15:25.592 --> 15:26.559
MR. PITTMAN --

15:26.593 --> 15:29.329
UHP, UHP, UHP.
CALL ME MARSHALL.

15:29.362 --> 15:31.531
MARSHALL.

15:31.564 --> 15:34.501
I'M ASSUMING THAT YOU HAVE
SOME PRESSING ISSUES --

15:34.534 --> 15:36.503
I NEED SOME FEEDBACK
ON MY PERSONNEL.

15:36.536 --> 15:39.506
COACH -- HE'S A LITTLE OCD,
DON'T YOU THINK?

15:39.539 --> 15:42.575
AND DONNALLY,
THE TRAINER --

15:42.609 --> 15:45.378
I HEAR SOME GYM EQUIPMENT
HAS GONE MISSING.

15:45.412 --> 15:47.547
I'M THINKING KLEPTO.

15:47.580 --> 15:50.383
I WOULDN'T KNOW.
THEY'RE NOT MY PATIENTS.

15:50.417 --> 15:52.352
BUT TERRENCE KING IS.

15:53.353 --> 15:55.555
I'M A THERAPIST. I CAN'T TALK
TO YOU ABOUT MY PATIENTS.

15:55.588 --> 15:58.124
YOU ARE AWARE
THAT I HAVE TO MAKE A DECISION

15:58.158 --> 15:59.526
ABOUT T.K.'s FUTURE SOON --

15:59.559 --> 16:02.328
A $7 MILLION DECISION.

16:02.362 --> 16:03.263
JUST AS<i>YOU</i>ARE AWARE

16:03.296 --> 16:06.533
THAT MY PATIENTS' RECORDS
ARE CONFIDENTIAL.

16:06.566 --> 16:09.636
YOU'RE NOT SCARED OF ME,
ARE YOU?

16:16.509 --> 16:17.544
SHOULD I BE?

16:17.577 --> 16:19.446
WELL,
I<i>AM</i>YOUR BOSS.

16:19.479 --> 16:22.415
AND WITH THE FINANCIAL PRESSURES
OF A DIVORCE...

16:22.449 --> 16:24.584
[ Chuckling ] I SEE
YOU'VE DONE YOUR HOMEWORK ON ME.

16:24.617 --> 16:27.554
OH, HO! I WAS TALKING
ABOUT<i>MY</i>DIVORCE.

16:27.587 --> 16:31.358
BUT SINCE WE SEEM TO HAVE
STUMBLED ON SOME COMMON GROUND,

16:31.391 --> 16:34.527
WHAT SAY WE POP OPEN
THIS MOUTON ROTHSCHILD

16:34.561 --> 16:36.563
AND GRIPE ABOUT OUR EXES?

16:36.596 --> 16:38.598
WELL,
THAT WOULD BE A "NO."

16:39.632 --> 16:41.601
TO T.K.'s RECORDS
<i>AND</i>TO THE WINE.

16:41.634 --> 16:43.370
SHAME.

16:43.403 --> 16:47.507
I<i>DO</i>LIKE TO GET TO KNOW
MY EMPLOYEES PERSONALLY.

16:47.540 --> 16:51.578
WHILE THEY'RE STILL
WORKING FOR ME, THAT IS.

16:56.716 --> 17:01.554
I LOVE MY JOB.
AND I CARE ABOUT THE PLAYERS.

17:01.588 --> 17:03.523
BUT I'M NOT
A GAME PLAYER.

17:03.556 --> 17:06.192
SO IF YOU'RE GONNA FIRE ME
OVER THIS,

17:06.226 --> 17:10.463
FEEL FREE TO DO IT
RIGHT NOW.

17:12.499 --> 17:13.633
WELL, THEN.

17:13.667 --> 17:16.569
I GUESS
THE NEXT MOVE IS MINE.

17:20.840 --> 17:23.643
1974.

17:23.677 --> 17:30.684
I HOPE YOU AND WHATEVER...
FRIEND YOU WERE EXPECTING

17:30.717 --> 17:32.686
ENJOY IT.

17:34.587 --> 17:37.691
I'LL LET MYSELF OUT.

17:50.870 --> 17:53.606
I'M LOOKING
FOR DERRICK LISTON.

17:55.608 --> 17:59.579
DERRICK'S OUT OF TOWN --
ON BUSINESS.

17:59.612 --> 18:03.616
AND YOU'RE HIS, UH, SISTER,
RIGHT -- ZETTY?

18:03.650 --> 18:04.584
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

18:04.617 --> 18:06.519
BACK OFF OF T.K.

18:07.554 --> 18:10.590
LAST I CHECKED,
T.K. WAS A BIG BOY --

18:10.623 --> 18:11.791
PICKED HIS OWN FRIENDS.

18:11.825 --> 18:14.661
WELL, YOU KNOW, FRIENDS DON'T
GIVE OTHER FRIENDS DIRTY GUNS.

18:14.694 --> 18:17.530
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:17.564 --> 18:19.599
LEAST HE DIDN'T
WALK OUT THAT CONVENTION

18:19.632 --> 18:21.668
WITH TWO PIECES OF LEAD
IN HIM.

18:24.571 --> 18:25.939
WE CAME UP WITH TERRENCE.

18:25.972 --> 18:28.508
WE KNOW
HOW TO PROTECT HIM.

18:28.541 --> 18:29.809
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU MEAN<i>YOU.</i>

18:29.843 --> 18:32.545
DERRICK'S UPSTATE --
ATTICA.

18:32.579 --> 18:34.547
<i>YOU</i>HANDLED THE GUNS.

18:36.649 --> 18:39.586
I'D HATE TO SEE YOU END UP
BEHIND BARS, LIKE YOUR BROTHER.

18:42.555 --> 18:43.723
INTERESTING CHOICE.

18:48.928 --> 18:52.699
Ray Jr.: THE AVERAGE AGE
OF CONSENT IN EUROPE IS 16.

18:52.732 --> 18:55.702
ROMEO AND JULIET --
THEIR PARENTS KEPT THEM APART.

18:55.735 --> 18:57.303
AND LOOK
WHAT HAPPENED TO<i>THEM.</i>

18:57.337 --> 18:58.705
YOU'RE FIGHTING BIOLOGY.

18:58.738 --> 19:00.940
NOT TO MENTION
SHAKESPEARE.

19:00.974 --> 19:02.108
LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT.

19:02.142 --> 19:05.912
ARE -- ARE YOU ASKING PERMISSION
TO HAVE SEX IN MY HOUSE?

19:05.945 --> 19:07.647
THAT'S -- THAT'S
THE TOPIC SENTENCE, YES.

19:07.681 --> 19:08.715
AH.

19:08.748 --> 19:10.583
WHERE WOULD YOU
LIKE US TO GO?

19:10.617 --> 19:12.686
THE WOODS?

19:13.687 --> 19:15.955
TO A FLEA BAG MOTEL?

19:15.989 --> 19:18.725
MOM, THE TRUTH IS,
YOU'RE NOT GONNA STOP US, OKAY?

19:18.758 --> 19:21.594
SO WHY LIVE IN DENIAL
AND PUT US AT FURTHER RISK

19:21.628 --> 19:24.664
WHEN THE SAFEST PLACE FOR US
IS RIGHT IN OUR OWN HOME?

19:29.602 --> 19:30.637
YEAH.

19:30.670 --> 19:34.607
I APPRECIATE THIS MATURE ATTEMPT
TO CHANGE MY MIND.

19:34.641 --> 19:36.876
I REALLY DO.
IT'S AWFULLY IMPRESSIVE.

19:36.910 --> 19:37.877
SO, DOES --
SO, DOES THAT MEAN --

19:37.911 --> 19:39.012
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

19:39.045 --> 19:41.614
'CAUSE AS COMPELLING
AS THAT WAS,

19:41.648 --> 19:43.516
YOU ARE NOT
AN ADULT YET.

19:43.550 --> 19:46.720
'CAUSE I'M LIKE, WHAT --
9 MONTHS AWAY FROM BEING 18?

19:46.753 --> 19:47.954
RAY JAY.

19:47.987 --> 19:50.657
THERE IS
THIS EMOTIONAL CONNECTION

19:50.690 --> 19:52.959
THAT SHOULD GO ALONG
WITH SEX.

19:52.992 --> 19:55.695
YOU AND OLIVIA
BARELY EVEN KNOW EACH OTHER.

19:55.729 --> 19:59.032
I FEEL LIKE IT WOULD BE
IRRESPONSIBLE OF ME

19:59.065 --> 20:02.635
TO PROMOTE SOMETHING
THAT I DON'T APPROVE OF.

20:02.669 --> 20:04.604
NOT TO MENTION SOMETHING
THAT OLIVIA'S MOTHER

20:04.637 --> 20:06.639
ALSO PROBABLY DOESN'T
APPROVE OF.

20:06.673 --> 20:08.908
YEAH? WELL, SHE'S WAY COOLER
THAN YOU, SO...

20:08.942 --> 20:10.677
I'M SURE SHE IS!

20:13.713 --> 20:15.382
Matthew:
GOOD. GOOD. GOOD.

20:15.415 --> 20:17.050
COME ON, DRIVE, DRIVE,
DRIVE, DRIVE, DRIVE, DRIVE.

20:17.083 --> 20:17.984
[ GRUNTS ]

20:18.018 --> 20:20.553
COME ON, DRIVE, DRIVE,
DRIVE, DRIVE, DRIVE.

20:22.422 --> 20:23.923
ALL RIGHT.
YOUR SPEED'S GOOD.

20:23.957 --> 20:25.558
YOUR SPEED'S GOOD, MAN.

20:25.592 --> 20:26.993
LATERAL MOVEMENT'S
THE LAST THING TO COME.

20:27.027 --> 20:29.596
YOU'LL GET IT ALL BACK --
AND MORE. YOU'LL BE FASTER.

20:29.629 --> 20:30.730
YEAH, ESPECIALLY
WITH MY CHEERLEADERS.

20:30.764 --> 20:32.665
CONRAD.

20:32.699 --> 20:33.667
DROP IT
LIKE IT'S HOT.

20:33.700 --> 20:34.668
[ LAUGHS ]
[ BEAT-BOXES ]

20:34.701 --> 20:35.935
DIRK.

20:35.969 --> 20:37.904
WIGGLE, WIGGLE, WIGGLE,
WIGGLE, WIGGLE, WIGGLE!

20:37.937 --> 20:39.673
LISTEN.
NOTHING, HUH? DAMN.

20:39.706 --> 20:42.409
YOU KNOW, WE'RE 10 WEEKS OUT
FROM MINI-CAMP, ALL RIGHT?

20:42.442 --> 20:45.011
WE GOT TIME, BUT WE GOT TO WORK.
ALL RIGHT? NO SLACKING.

20:45.045 --> 20:47.947
GRAB A DRINK, AND THEN
LET'S HIT THE LADDER. OKAY?

20:47.981 --> 20:49.649
I THINK I'M DONE
FOR TODAY.

20:49.683 --> 20:50.583
NO, T.,
WE JUST SAID NO SLACKING.

20:50.617 --> 20:52.652
COME ON, MAN. NOW'S THE TIME.
WE GOT TO GO.

20:52.686 --> 20:54.654
YEAH, WELL,
THIS HORSE IS DONE RUNNING.

20:54.688 --> 20:56.022
[ CUP CLATTERS ]

21:00.994 --> 21:02.762
SENSE MEMORY?

21:02.796 --> 21:05.065
IT'S MEMORY OF A TRAUMA
FROM YOUR PAST

21:05.098 --> 21:07.701
THAT CAUSES YOU TO HAVE
A PHYSICAL REACTION

21:07.734 --> 21:08.601
IN YOUR PRESENT.

21:08.635 --> 21:12.739
SENSORY MEMORIES CAN BE
TO SIGHT, SOUND,

21:12.772 --> 21:14.674
OR, IN YOUR CASE...

21:14.708 --> 21:16.743
A SMELL.

21:16.776 --> 21:19.979
AND YOU THINK LUCI GETTING HURT
WAS A TRIGGER?

21:20.013 --> 21:21.948
APPEARS SO.

21:21.981 --> 21:24.751
WHAT'S YOUR RELATIONSHIP LIKE
WITH LUCI?

21:24.784 --> 21:25.985
WELL,
SHE'S MY DERBY WIFE.

21:26.019 --> 21:26.953
OH.

21:26.986 --> 21:28.922
IT'S THE SKATER
THAT YOU'RE TIGHTEST WITH --

21:28.955 --> 21:29.989
WHO HAS YOUR BACK.

21:30.023 --> 21:31.725
OH.

21:31.758 --> 21:32.692
SO, YOU'RE NOT --

21:32.726 --> 21:33.560
NO. [ LAUGHS ]

21:33.593 --> 21:36.696
MORE LIKE A SISTER
THAN ANYTHING ELSE.

21:36.730 --> 21:39.032
DOES YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH LUCI

21:39.065 --> 21:42.736
BRING UP MEMORIES
OF ANYONE ELSE IN YOUR LIFE?

21:42.769 --> 21:43.737
MAYBE YOUR SISTER?

21:43.770 --> 21:44.637
DEFINITELY NOT. NO.

21:44.671 --> 21:46.806
I MEAN, WE WERE TIGHT
WHEN WE WERE LITTLE,

21:46.840 --> 21:47.607
LIKE ANY KIDS --

21:47.640 --> 21:49.743
YOU KNOW,
JUNGLE GYM, COLORING --

21:49.776 --> 21:51.711
BUT I SEE HER
LIKE TWICE A YEAR NOW.

21:51.745 --> 21:53.713
HMM.

21:53.747 --> 21:55.749
AND NO ONE ELSE
COMES TO MIND?

21:55.782 --> 21:59.486
I CAN'T THINK OF ANYONE
THAT REMINDS ME OF LUCI.

21:59.519 --> 22:00.754
IT'S YOUR CONSCIOUS MIND

22:00.787 --> 22:02.756
NOT WANTING
TO MAKE A CONNECTION.

22:02.789 --> 22:04.991
SO, NOW WHAT?

22:05.025 --> 22:07.727
HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT HYPNOSIS?

22:14.734 --> 22:15.769
OH.

22:15.802 --> 22:17.771
HOLA, DONNALLY.

22:17.804 --> 22:18.571
SCOTCH IN THE DRAWER.

22:18.605 --> 22:20.707
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]
HELP YOURSELF.

22:20.740 --> 22:22.776
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
OH, WAIT. YOU ALREADY HAVE.

22:22.809 --> 22:25.845
WE HAVE GOT TO WORK
ON REFINING YOUR PALATE.

22:25.879 --> 22:29.783
I'VE HAD PAINT THINNER
WITH MORE CHARACTER THAN THIS.

22:30.784 --> 22:32.152
NO.
I'M ON THE CLOCK.

22:32.185 --> 22:34.754
OLD SCHOOL.
BUSINESS FIRST.

22:34.788 --> 22:36.189
LIKE THE YAKUZA.

22:36.222 --> 22:39.092
YOU'RE NOT JAPANESE,
ARE YOU?

22:44.798 --> 22:46.800
HOW DID HIS WORKOUT GO?

22:46.833 --> 22:48.134
WHO, T.K.?

22:48.168 --> 22:49.769
WELL, YOU SAW HIM.

22:49.803 --> 22:53.707
I NEED
A<i>PROFESSIONAL</i>OPINION.

22:53.740 --> 22:56.109
WELL, I THOUGHT
HE LOOKED GREAT, CONSIDERING.

22:56.142 --> 22:58.011
HE'S AHEAD
OF HIS TIMELINE.

22:59.045 --> 23:01.848
BUT, AS YOU SAW,
STILL SOME WORK TO DO.

23:01.881 --> 23:04.551
YOU EVER PLAY THE PONIES,
DONNALLY? I NEED A NUMBER.

23:04.584 --> 23:05.585
THIS ISN'T A HORSE.

23:05.618 --> 23:07.754
I CAN'T GIVE YOU THE ODDS
OF A PERSON'S RECOVERY.

23:09.856 --> 23:12.859
WHAT I<i>CAN</i>TELL YOU
IS WHAT YOU ALREADY KNOW --

23:12.892 --> 23:14.227
THAT T.K.
IS A RARE TALENT.

23:14.260 --> 23:16.796
PLAYERS LIKE HIM
DON'T COME AROUND VERY OFTEN.

23:16.830 --> 23:18.765
OR GET SHOT
IN THE LUNG AND LEG.

23:18.798 --> 23:21.101
NO.

23:21.134 --> 23:23.203
LET ME TELL YOU THIS --

23:23.236 --> 23:25.205
TERRENCE KING ON ONE LEG
IS BETTER

23:25.238 --> 23:27.207
THAN 95% OF THE RECEIVERS
IN THIS LEAGUE.

23:27.240 --> 23:29.075
YOU WANT A NUMBER?

23:29.109 --> 23:31.845
THERE'S YOUR NUMBER.

23:33.613 --> 23:35.115
[ LAUGHING ]

23:38.785 --> 23:40.820
AHHH.

23:40.854 --> 23:44.758
IF I DON'T SEE THE GOODS,
THEN I'M NOT PAYING FOR THEM.

23:44.791 --> 23:46.826
EITHER T.K.
IS GOOD TO GO ON FRIDAY

23:46.860 --> 23:49.529
OR HE'S DONE.

23:53.266 --> 23:58.204
HE COULD DO ANYTHING TO ANYONE
JUST FOR SPORT.

23:58.238 --> 24:01.074
HE COULD, AND HE DOES.

24:01.107 --> 24:02.275
BUT HE WON'T DO IT TO<i>YOU.</i>
TRUST ME.

24:02.308 --> 24:06.846
HE KNOWS THAT YOU HAVE SAVED
HIS TEAM'S ASS PLENTY OF TIMES.

24:06.880 --> 24:08.114
AND WHAT I DO WANT
TO KNOW

24:08.148 --> 24:10.150
IS WHAT'S GOING ON
BETWEEN HIM AND NICO.

24:10.183 --> 24:13.820
IS THERE SOME COMPLICATED
HISTORY WITH THOSE TWO?

24:13.853 --> 24:14.854
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]
COMPLICATED?
YEAH.

24:14.888 --> 24:16.222
OH, NO!

24:16.256 --> 24:18.058
THAT'S PROBABLY PITTMAN
TRYING TO SLEEP WITH YOU AGAIN.

24:18.091 --> 24:20.160
HA HA.
YOU'RE FUNNY.

24:22.162 --> 24:23.163
NO, NO.
IT'S RAY JAY.

24:23.196 --> 24:26.032
HE'S, UH, SPENDING THE NIGHT
AT HIS FRIEND'S HOUSE

24:26.066 --> 24:26.866
INSTEAD OF RAY'S.

24:26.900 --> 24:29.102
YOU MEAN
AT HIS GIRLFRIEND'S HOUSE?

24:29.135 --> 24:31.171
EW. GOD, NO. WHAT KIND OF MOTHER
DO YOU THINK I AM?

24:31.204 --> 24:32.172
A NAIVE ONE?

24:32.205 --> 24:35.809
DANI, COME ON.
THE KID'S 17.

24:35.842 --> 24:37.811
HE'S GOT A GIRLFRIEND
WHO WANTS TO HAVE SEX WITH HIM.

24:37.844 --> 24:39.279
LIKE, SHE'S BEGGING HIM
FOR SEX.

24:39.312 --> 24:41.848
[ High-pitched ] RAY JAY,
PLEASE HAVE SEX WITH ME.

24:41.881 --> 24:44.117
[ Normal voice ]
AND YOU SAID THAT HE COULDN'T
DO IT IN THE HOUSE.

24:44.150 --> 24:45.251
I MEAN,
BY THE LAWS OF MANHOOD,

24:45.285 --> 24:47.287
YOU'RE PRACTICALLY FORCING
THE KID TO IMPEACH HIMSELF.

24:47.320 --> 24:49.289
RAY JAY WOULDN'T LIE TO ME
ABOUT SOMETHING LIKE THIS.

24:49.322 --> 24:50.657
YOU KNOW WHAT?

24:50.690 --> 24:52.826
I HAPPEN TO HAVE
A HANDY LITTLE APP

24:52.859 --> 24:55.095
THAT WILL LOCATE HIS PHONE

24:55.128 --> 24:58.131
AND PROVE TO YOU
THAT HE IS, IN FACT, AT --

25:05.038 --> 25:06.072
YOU SHOULD GO.
WHAT?

25:06.106 --> 25:06.906
YEP.
NO!

25:06.940 --> 25:09.342
I AM GONNA GO GET
THAT LITTLE ROMEO,

25:09.376 --> 25:18.885
AND HE IS GONNA<i>WISH</i>
HE DRANK POISON!

25:18.918 --> 25:20.720
YOU ARE GROUNDED
FOR A MONTH!

25:20.754 --> 25:22.322
GIVE ME YOUR KEYS.
WHAT? NO, NO, NO.

25:22.355 --> 25:23.890
YOU DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT STAYING AT OLIVIA'S HOUSE.

25:23.923 --> 25:25.792
OH, AND HER MOM<i>DID?</i>

25:25.825 --> 25:28.695
WELL, SHE FOUND THAT PowerPoint
VERY PERSUASIVE, MOM.

25:28.728 --> 25:29.896
RAY JAY,
YOU LIED TO ME.

25:29.929 --> 25:31.898
WELL, I TRIED NOT TO, OKAY?
AND LOOK WHERE THAT GOT ME.

25:31.931 --> 25:32.966
GIVE ME YOUR DAMN KEYS.

25:32.999 --> 25:34.801
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU'RE A HYPOCRITE.

25:34.834 --> 25:36.036
DON'T TRY TO PRETEND
THAT YOU AND DAD

25:36.069 --> 25:37.904
WEREN'T DOING THIS
IN HIGH SCHOOL.

25:37.937 --> 25:38.905
OBJECTION! IRRELEVANT!

25:38.938 --> 25:39.839
COMPLETELY RELEVANT,
OKAY?

25:39.873 --> 25:40.674
SEX IS NORMAL.

25:40.707 --> 25:42.909
DAD'S NOT FREAKING OUT
ABOUT THIS.

25:42.942 --> 25:44.911
AH.
AND WHAT ARE YOU
SO WORRIED ABOUT?

25:44.944 --> 25:46.846
YOU REALLY WANT TO KNOW?
[ Chuckling ] OKAY.

25:46.880 --> 25:49.015
SEE,
IT'S ALL FUN AND GAMES

25:49.049 --> 25:51.017
UNTIL YOU GET
YOUR LITTLE GIRLFRIEND PREGNANT.

25:51.051 --> 25:52.919
RIGHT? THEN WHAT?
YOU'RE 17.

25:52.952 --> 25:54.921
YOU CAN'T GET INTO
A GOOD COLLEGE

25:54.954 --> 25:56.856
'CAUSE --
OH, YEAH! GUESS WHAT!

25:56.890 --> 25:58.925
YOU KNOCKED UP
YOUR S.A.T. TUTOR!

25:58.958 --> 26:01.861
OH, AND THEN YOU'RE WORKING
AT SOME GREASY FAST-FOOD JOINT,

26:01.895 --> 26:02.762
BUT IT'S NOT ENOUGH

26:02.796 --> 26:06.399
FOR BABY FOOD AND CAR SEATS
AND DIAPERS.

26:06.433 --> 26:07.567
AND THEN
YOU GET DESPERATE.

26:07.600 --> 26:10.804
"OH, OFFICER, I'M SORRY
I WAS STEALING THOSE PEACHES.

26:10.837 --> 26:11.938
I'M JUST
A TEEN BABY DADDY."

26:11.971 --> 26:13.773
AND THEN,
NEXT THING YOU KNOW,

26:13.807 --> 26:15.775
YOU'RE DOING 15 TO LIFE
IN SING SING!

26:15.809 --> 26:16.976
SO, YOU'RE SAYING
SEX LEADS TO PRISON.

26:17.010 --> 26:19.412
YES, I AM!
PUT IT IN YOUR PowerPoint!

26:19.446 --> 26:20.547
WHY DON'T YOU
JUST SAY IT, MOM?

26:20.580 --> 26:21.948
[ SIGHS ]
WHY DON'T YOU JUST SAY
YOU DON'T WANT ME

26:21.981 --> 26:23.817
TO END UP
LIKE YOU AND DAD?

26:23.850 --> 26:27.854
KNOCKED UP, YOUNG,
AND IN A CRAPPY MARRIAGE.

26:31.424 --> 26:32.959
I'M JUST TRYING
TO PROTECT YOU.

26:38.998 --> 26:40.400
MAYBE YOU CAN'T.

26:50.010 --> 26:52.746
[ GRUNTS ] OHH!
SON OF A BITCH.

26:52.779 --> 26:53.680
I CAN'T EVEN RUN
A 5-YARD SLAM, MAN.

26:53.713 --> 26:55.782
WE'RE GOOD, ALL RIGHT?
WE'RE GOOD FOR TODAY.

26:55.815 --> 26:56.783
YOU STRETCH IT OUT,

26:56.816 --> 26:58.785
GIVE IT A LITTLE ICE MASSAGE,
AND WE'RE DONE.

26:58.818 --> 26:59.953
ALL RIGHT?

26:59.986 --> 27:01.821
LOOK, MAN,
THE GAME'S 80% MENTAL.

27:01.855 --> 27:02.989
THIS WILL COME.

27:03.023 --> 27:04.858
YEAH, AND PITTMAN'S SWEATING ME
LIKE A HOOKER IN CHURCH,

27:04.891 --> 27:06.826
SO HOW AM I SUPPOSED TO BE
ALL MENTAL, HUH?

27:06.860 --> 27:09.963
[ GROANS ]

27:09.996 --> 27:10.997
WELL, FORTUNATELY,

27:11.031 --> 27:13.767
YOU KNOW SOMEBODY
THAT CAN HELP YOU WITH THAT.

27:13.800 --> 27:14.934
OH.

27:14.968 --> 27:16.936
THERE SHE IS --
OPRAH HERSELF.

27:16.970 --> 27:18.104
[ PATS LEG ]

27:18.138 --> 27:20.940
I'M GOOD TO GO.
GOOD TO GO. THANKS.

27:20.974 --> 27:21.908
HEY, TERRENCE.

27:21.941 --> 27:24.077
WHAT'S UP, DOC?
AIN'T NOTHING TO TALK ABOUT.

27:24.110 --> 27:27.914
IF I DON'T PERFORM,
I GET CUT.

27:27.947 --> 27:30.016
GET CUT,
MY LIFE IS OVER.

27:30.050 --> 27:30.984
HEY.

27:31.017 --> 27:33.920
AS LONG AS YOU'RE ALIVE,
YOUR LIFE IS NOT OVER.

27:33.953 --> 27:35.889
I THINK
YOU'VE LEARNED THAT MUCH.

27:35.922 --> 27:36.756
[ LAUGHS ]

27:36.790 --> 27:39.025
THAT'S WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT, SEE?

27:39.059 --> 27:40.894
YOU --
TALKING TO PEOPLE.

27:40.927 --> 27:41.928
THAT'S WHAT YOU DO.

27:41.961 --> 27:44.898
IT'S YOUR JOB,
RIGHT?

27:44.931 --> 27:47.901
AND JUST LIKE
MOST PEOPLE...

27:47.934 --> 27:49.803
THEIR JOB
IS WHAT THEY DO.

27:49.836 --> 27:53.039
FOOTBALL IS EVERYTHING I GOT.
IT'S WHAT I DO.

27:53.073 --> 27:54.941
YOU KNOW,
AND IF THAT'S EVERYTHING

27:54.974 --> 27:57.310
AND THAT GETS CUT FROM ME,
WHAT ELSE I GOT?

27:57.344 --> 27:58.945
I GOT SIX LOCKS
ON MY DOOR.

27:58.978 --> 28:00.980
I GOT BODYGUARDS
OUTSIDE MY WINDOW.

28:01.014 --> 28:01.915
AND ALL FOR WHAT?

28:01.948 --> 28:03.917
I KEEP WAKING UP
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT

28:03.950 --> 28:04.951
IN COLD SWEATS.

28:04.984 --> 28:08.922
AIN'T NOBODY GIVING THAT DUDE
$7 MILLION. COME ON.

28:08.955 --> 28:09.956
TERRENCE.

28:09.989 --> 28:11.124
[ SIGHS ]

28:11.157 --> 28:15.995
I THINK THAT IF YOU START
TO TALK ABOUT YOUR FEELINGS,

28:16.029 --> 28:18.932
THEN YOU'LL HEAL
FASTER --

28:18.965 --> 28:20.500
PHYSICALLY<i>AND</i>MENTALLY.

28:21.901 --> 28:23.069
YEAH, WELL, SORRY, DOC.

28:23.103 --> 28:25.138
TOMORROW'S THE END
OF MY CAREER.

28:25.171 --> 28:27.140
I GOT NOTHING TO WEAR.

28:27.173 --> 28:29.909
I AIN'T GOT TIME
FOR THIS.

28:32.846 --> 28:35.148
HEY.
I NEED A FAVOR.

28:35.181 --> 28:36.883
YOU GOT TO TALK
TO PITTMAN.

28:36.916 --> 28:39.085
T.K.'s NOT READY FOR THIS.
HE IS COMING APART OUT THERE.

28:39.119 --> 28:41.087
WELL, IT'S<i>HIS</i>SHIP.
HE GETS TO STEER IT.

28:41.121 --> 28:43.957
WELL, HE'S GONNA STEER US
RIGHT INTO A FREAKIN' ICEBERG.

28:43.990 --> 28:45.225
GOD,
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOU?

28:45.258 --> 28:47.193
WHAT DOES PITTMAN HAVE ON YOU,
ANYWAY?

28:47.227 --> 28:48.962
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:48.995 --> 28:51.965
GOT THIS UNDYING,
UNQUESTIONING LOYALTY.

28:51.998 --> 28:54.134
DON'T EVER QUESTION
MY LOYALTY.

28:54.167 --> 28:56.102
I'M NOT QUESTIONING
YOUR LOYALTY, NICO.

28:56.136 --> 28:58.938
I'M QUESTIONING
WHAT YOU'RE LOYAL<i>TO.</i>

29:00.840 --> 29:03.209
Dani: YOU'RE VIEWING THIS
LIKE A MOVIE, GRACE.

29:03.243 --> 29:05.945
WE'RE AT THE TRACK.

29:05.979 --> 29:07.947
TELL ME WHAT YOU SEE.

29:07.981 --> 29:11.084
I SEE LUCI.

29:11.117 --> 29:15.989
HER HELMET'S LOOSE,
SO...I TIGHTEN IT FOR HER.

29:16.022 --> 29:17.924
<i>MAKE SURE SHE'S SAFE.</i>

29:19.025 --> 29:23.163
TELL ME MORE ABOUT LUCI.

29:23.196 --> 29:25.031
SHE'S MY JAMMER.

29:25.065 --> 29:27.000
SHE'S MY BEST FRIEND.

29:27.033 --> 29:30.970
IT'S MY JOB
TO PROTECT HER.

29:31.004 --> 29:32.072
AND I DIDN'T THAT DAY.

29:35.041 --> 29:39.012
WHEN SHE GOT HIT
OFF THE TRACK.

29:39.045 --> 29:40.947
LET'S GO BACK
TO THAT MOMENT.

29:40.980 --> 29:43.149
[ Voice breaking ]<i>SHE'S GONE.</i>
<i>I CAN'T SEE HER.</i>

29:43.183 --> 29:47.020
TELL ME HOW YOU FEEL
WHEN YOU CAN'T SEE HER.

29:47.053 --> 29:48.121
HELPLESS.

29:48.154 --> 29:50.924
[ GASPING ]

29:50.957 --> 29:53.026
IT'S ALL MY FAULT.

29:56.062 --> 29:59.032
THE -- THE SMELL.

29:59.065 --> 30:00.133
IT'S HERE.

30:01.935 --> 30:03.103
OKAY.
THE SAME SMELL?

30:04.137 --> 30:05.138
YES.

30:07.907 --> 30:08.942
<i>IT'S SO STRONG.</i>

30:08.975 --> 30:10.877
THAT'S GOOD.
JUST STAY WITH IT.

30:10.910 --> 30:12.912
GRACE, TELL ME
WHAT IT SMELLS LIKE.

30:12.946 --> 30:14.881
SWEET.

30:14.914 --> 30:16.016
BUT IT'S LIKE A CHEMICAL.

30:16.049 --> 30:18.018
IT'S OVERPOWERING.

30:18.051 --> 30:20.120
OKAY, IF THERE COULD BE
ONE WORD TO DESCRIBE IT,

30:20.153 --> 30:21.121
WHAT WOULD THAT BE?

30:21.154 --> 30:22.989
[ SIGHS ]

30:23.023 --> 30:23.957
JUST TRY.

30:23.990 --> 30:27.961
WHAT'S THE FIRST THING
THAT COMES TO YOUR MIND?

30:29.963 --> 30:30.964
CHILDHOOD.

30:32.966 --> 30:34.901
IT SMELLS
LIKE CHILDHOOD.

30:48.048 --> 30:49.983
[ GRUNTS ]

30:50.016 --> 30:52.952
AAH!

30:52.986 --> 30:56.056
Conrad:
YOU OKAY IN THERE, MR. KING?

30:56.089 --> 30:57.257
YEAH, I'M GOOD.

31:05.231 --> 31:07.133
HEY, YO.

31:07.167 --> 31:10.003
IT'S ME.

31:10.036 --> 31:12.672
I GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

31:12.706 --> 31:15.942
YOU ARE RUNNING YOUR BEST PLAYER
INTO THE GROUND.

31:15.975 --> 31:18.044
BECAUSE I WANT HIM
TO SHOW ME

31:18.078 --> 31:20.146
THAT HE IS FIT ENOUGH
TO SURVIVE.

31:20.180 --> 31:21.715
YOU'RE NOT PROTECTING
YOUR ASSETS.

31:21.748 --> 31:23.016
I MEAN, YOUR GAME
IS BIGGER THAN THAT.

31:23.049 --> 31:24.117
AND YOU'RE USING ME
TO PLAY IT.

31:24.150 --> 31:26.052
WHAT GAME IS THAT?

31:26.086 --> 31:28.054
WE HAVE BEEN THROUGH A LOT
TOGETHER, MARSHALL.

31:28.088 --> 31:29.155
BUT YOU CAN ONLY PUSH ME
SO FAR.

31:29.189 --> 31:31.157
WHO PUSHED WHOM, NICO?

31:31.191 --> 31:33.093
HAVE WE ALREADY FORGOTTEN?

31:33.126 --> 31:34.694
OKAY.

31:34.728 --> 31:36.062
YOU WANT TO DO THIS?

31:36.096 --> 31:37.964
LET'S DO IT --
RIGHT HERE, RIGHT NOW.

31:37.997 --> 31:39.199
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO KNOW?
WHAT? TELL ME.

31:39.232 --> 31:42.102
WHEN THE FIRST TIME WAS?
HOW LONG IT LASTED?

31:42.135 --> 31:43.937
HOW GOOD SHE WAS?

31:45.205 --> 31:47.073
SURE.

31:47.107 --> 31:48.141
FIRST TIME.

31:48.174 --> 31:50.744
HOTEL ROOM -- BRUSSELS.

31:50.777 --> 31:52.145
AND AFTER THAT?

31:52.178 --> 31:53.146
NEW YORK.

31:53.179 --> 31:55.015
AND THEN?
PARIS.

31:55.048 --> 31:56.716
THAT WAS THE END OF IT.

31:56.750 --> 31:58.051
HOW WAS SHE?

31:59.219 --> 32:01.087
Unbelievable.

32:04.124 --> 32:06.993
YES, SHE IS.

32:07.027 --> 32:08.028
YOU STILL
IN LOVE WITH HER?

32:08.061 --> 32:10.063
NO.

32:10.096 --> 32:11.131
ARE<i>YOU?</i>

32:12.599 --> 32:13.633
THAT'S PERSONAL.

32:13.667 --> 32:17.270
LET'S NOT FORGET --
I WAS IN LOVE WITH HER FIRST.

32:17.303 --> 32:19.139
BUT YOU COULDN'T
PULL THE TRIGGER.

32:19.172 --> 32:21.174
I GUESS I'M JUST NOT
THE MARRYING KIND.

32:21.207 --> 32:23.209
UNLIKE, UH...YOU.

32:23.243 --> 32:25.111
[ LAUGHS ]

32:25.145 --> 32:27.147
ARE WE DONE?

32:28.815 --> 32:30.050
AHH.<i>I</i>AM.

32:30.083 --> 32:32.052
TOMORROW, T.K.'s RUN --

32:32.085 --> 32:33.787
GO EASY ON HIM.

32:33.820 --> 32:37.457
THE GUY'S KILLING HIMSELF
FOR YOU.

32:37.490 --> 32:39.592
THAT'S WHAT HE GETS PAID
THE BIG BUCKS FOR.

32:39.626 --> 32:42.162
I AM GONNA SAVE THIS TEAM,
NICO.

32:42.195 --> 32:45.065
BUT I'M GONNA DO IT
<i>MY</i>WAY.

32:49.102 --> 32:51.037
GO, HAWKS!

32:51.071 --> 32:54.140
[ CROWD CHEERS ]

32:58.244 --> 32:59.813
HEY.

32:59.846 --> 33:01.081
GRACE.

33:01.114 --> 33:02.148
WHAT HAPPENED?

33:02.182 --> 33:03.817
[ Crying ]
I WAS FIRED FROM MY JOB.

33:03.850 --> 33:04.951
FROM THE SOFTWARE FIRM?

33:04.984 --> 33:07.187
I GOT IN A FIGHT WITH MY BOSS,
AND I THREW MY LAPTOP.

33:07.220 --> 33:10.156
I HAVE<i>NEVER</i>DONE ANYTHING
THAT VIOLENT --

33:10.190 --> 33:11.257
OFF THE TRACK.

33:11.291 --> 33:14.227
SOUNDS LIKE
YOU BROUGHT DisGrace KELLY

33:14.260 --> 33:15.362
TO THE OFFICE, HUH?

33:18.098 --> 33:21.134
DERBY IS AN OUTLET
FOR ME.

33:21.167 --> 33:23.269
IT IS WHAT MAKES ME
SUCH A GREAT BLOCKER.

33:23.303 --> 33:25.338
CAN'T YOU JUST TELL NITRO
TO PUT ME BACK IN?

33:25.372 --> 33:27.107
TRUTHFULLY,
DO YOU REALLY THINK

33:27.140 --> 33:29.109
THAT YOU'RE READY
TO GO BACK OUT THERE?

33:29.142 --> 33:30.810
I NEED TO GET
BACK ON MY SKATES.

33:30.844 --> 33:32.278
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA
HELP ME WITH THAT.

33:32.312 --> 33:34.114
I'M TRYING.

33:34.147 --> 33:36.082
AND -- AND BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
AND -- AND BELIEVE IT OR NOT,
<i>HAV</i>MADE PROGRESS.

33:36.116 --> 33:40.086
REALLY?! BECAUSE I'VE LOST
MY JOB, AND I'M SITTING
ON THE SIDELINES.

33:40.120 --> 33:42.155
SO YOU TELL ME
HOW ANY OF THAT IS PROGRESS.

33:42.188 --> 33:43.823
I NEED TO KNOW

33:43.857 --> 33:45.525
WHY THE HELL ANY OF THIS
IS EVEN HAPPENING TO ME.

33:45.558 --> 33:46.659
LISTEN TO ME.

33:46.693 --> 33:48.495
WHEN YOU WERE
UNDER HYPNOSIS,

33:48.528 --> 33:52.065
I ASKED YOU TO DESCRIBE
THE SMELL WITH ONE WORD.

33:53.199 --> 33:56.336
OKAY?
AND YOU SAID, "CHILDHOOD."

33:57.337 --> 33:59.506
I DID.

33:59.539 --> 34:03.143
SOMEWHERE IN YOUR CHILDHOOD
IS THE ANSWER --

34:03.176 --> 34:04.277
TO ALL OF IT.

34:04.310 --> 34:06.146
BUT I ALREADY TOLD YOU.

34:06.179 --> 34:09.215
MY MOM WAS A DRUNK.
MY FATHER WAS ABSENT.

34:09.249 --> 34:11.484
MY SISTER'S
IN A WHEELCHAIR.

34:11.518 --> 34:13.687
SHE WAS IN A CAR ACCIDENT
WHEN SHE WAS 3.

34:13.720 --> 34:16.156
WE ARE GETTING CLOSE
TO SOMETHING,

34:16.189 --> 34:18.158
AND THAT'S WHY
YOU'RE SO AGITATED.

34:18.191 --> 34:20.160
YOU'RE BLOCKING
SOMETHING OUT.

34:20.193 --> 34:21.127
BUT WHAT?

34:21.161 --> 34:22.495
THAT'S WHAT WE'RE TRYING
TO FIGURE OUT, GRACE.

34:22.529 --> 34:24.130
THEN FIGURE IT OUT,
DAMN IT!

34:24.164 --> 34:27.701
BEFORE SOMETHING ELSE TERRIBLE
HAPPENS!

34:27.734 --> 34:29.536
Nico: T.K.?

34:29.569 --> 34:32.172
T.K.!

34:33.740 --> 34:36.242
CHECK THESE OTHER ROOMS,
OKAY?

34:38.745 --> 34:42.482
HEY. YEAH. IT'S ME.

34:48.355 --> 34:49.089
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU CAN'T FIND HIM?

34:50.657 --> 34:53.193
ALL RIGHT. KEEP LOOKING.
I'LL FIGURE IT OUT HERE.

34:53.226 --> 34:55.595
WELL,
IS HE THE INVISIBLE MAN?

34:55.628 --> 34:57.831
HE HAD A MINOR SETBACK
YESTERDAY, MARSHALL.

34:57.864 --> 34:59.199
HE INJURED HIMSELF.

34:59.232 --> 35:00.266
SO I HEARD.

35:00.300 --> 35:02.836
LOOK, IF YOU WANT A FAIR
EVALUATION OF HIS ABILITIES,

35:02.869 --> 35:04.304
THEN WE GOT TO PUSH THIS.

35:04.337 --> 35:06.439
THAT WON'T BE NECESSARY.

35:06.473 --> 35:08.775
CALL A PRESS CONFERENCE
FOR 11:59 A.M.

35:08.808 --> 35:10.677
I HAVE SEEN EVERYTHING --

35:10.710 --> 35:13.279
I SHOULD SAY
<i>NOT</i>SEEN EVERYTHING --

35:13.313 --> 35:14.647
I NEED TO SEE.

35:14.681 --> 35:16.716
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

35:16.750 --> 35:18.451
DID YOU SEND IT?

35:18.485 --> 35:19.819
I DIDN'T GET IT.

35:30.230 --> 35:31.631
HM.

35:36.736 --> 35:37.771
[ TOY SQUEAKS ]

35:37.804 --> 35:40.840
Dani:<i>WHAT'S YOUR RELATIONSHIP</i>
<i>WITH LUCI?</i>

35:40.874 --> 35:43.677
<i>MORE LIKE A SISTER</i>
<i>THAN ANYTHING ELSE.</i>

35:43.710 --> 35:44.678
<i>THE SMELL.</i>

35:46.880 --> 35:48.648
<i>SWEET.</i>

35:50.684 --> 35:51.885
<i>BUT IT'S LIKE A CHEMICAL.</i>

35:54.354 --> 35:59.859
YOU SAID THAT LUCI WAS
LIKE A SISTER TO YOU

35:59.893 --> 36:01.828
AND THAT IT WAS YOUR JOB
TO PROTECT HER.

36:01.861 --> 36:03.730
YEAH.
I ALREADY TOLD YOU THAT.

36:03.763 --> 36:05.865
JUST...BEAR WITH ME.

36:05.899 --> 36:10.337
YOU SAID THAT YOUR SISTER
WAS HIT BY A CAR,

36:10.370 --> 36:13.340
BUT YOU NEVER DESCRIBED
THE DETAILS,

36:13.373 --> 36:17.711
SO I WAS WONDERING...
WHAT HAPPENED.

36:17.744 --> 36:19.346
WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH ANYTHING?

36:19.379 --> 36:20.914
SOMETHING THAT HAPPENED
20 YEARS AGO?

36:20.947 --> 36:25.251
GRACE, WHERE WERE YOU
DURING THE ACCIDENT?

36:25.285 --> 36:27.287
[ SIGHS ]

36:27.320 --> 36:31.524
I WAS...OUTSIDE.

36:31.558 --> 36:32.826
WITH EMILY.

36:32.859 --> 36:34.694
YOUR LITTLE SISTER?

36:35.729 --> 36:36.563
YES.

36:36.596 --> 36:40.367
MY MOM WENT IN
TO GET A DRINK -- BOOZE.

36:40.400 --> 36:42.702
SHE TOLD ME TO WATCH EM.
I WAS<i>ALWAYS</i>WATCHING HER.

36:44.838 --> 36:47.907
YOU WERE ALWAYS
<i>PROTECTING</i>HER.

36:52.779 --> 36:55.281
[ SCOFFS ]

36:55.315 --> 36:56.383
YEAH.

36:57.550 --> 37:01.721
EM WAS BORED WITH COLORING,
SO SHE WENT OUTSIDE TO PLAY.

37:01.755 --> 37:04.891
AND -- AND I WAS PUTTING
THE CAPS BACK ON THE MARKERS.

37:04.924 --> 37:09.062
AND THAT'S WHEN -- THAT'S WHEN
I HEARD THAT SOUND --

37:09.095 --> 37:11.831
OF -- OF THE CAR.

37:11.865 --> 37:13.333
[ Voice breaking ]
THEN MY MOM

37:13.366 --> 37:17.337
CAME RUNNING OUT
INTO THE STREET.

37:17.370 --> 37:20.907
AND MY SISTER...

37:20.940 --> 37:23.576
HER LEGS...

37:23.610 --> 37:25.845
THEY'RE NOT MOVING.

37:28.114 --> 37:29.783
ALL RIGHT.

37:29.816 --> 37:32.085
AND YOU WERE COLORING.

37:32.118 --> 37:33.787
WEREN'T YOU?

37:33.820 --> 37:35.321
YEAH.
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:35.355 --> 37:36.322
MM-HMM.

37:36.356 --> 37:39.359
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

37:41.895 --> 37:44.364
OH, MY GOD.

37:46.132 --> 37:48.401
THAT'S THE SMELL.

37:49.502 --> 37:51.838
THEY BLAMED ME,

37:51.871 --> 37:54.407
AND THEY TOLD ME
THAT IT WAS MY FAULT,

37:54.441 --> 37:59.446
THAT IT WAS MY JOB
TO PROTECT HER, AND I DIDN'T.

37:59.479 --> 38:00.914
LISTEN TO ME.

38:00.947 --> 38:04.884
YOU WERE A CHILD.
YOUR MOTHER WAS DRINKING.

38:04.918 --> 38:10.857
IT WAS<i>HER</i>JOB
TO PROTECT YOUR SISTER,

38:10.890 --> 38:12.492
NOT YOURS.

38:12.525 --> 38:14.461
BUT I WISH I COULD HAVE.

38:14.494 --> 38:17.630
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
I WISH I COULD --

38:17.664 --> 38:19.366
[ SIGHS ] I KNOW.

38:19.399 --> 38:21.368
[ SIGHS ]

38:21.401 --> 38:23.136
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

38:23.169 --> 38:24.504
YOU'RE GOOD.

38:24.537 --> 38:27.374
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

38:27.407 --> 38:28.842
[ SNIFFLES ]

38:30.410 --> 38:31.478
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

38:31.511 --> 38:33.113
HEY.

38:33.146 --> 38:34.514
HEY.

38:34.547 --> 38:35.515
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

38:35.548 --> 38:38.385
HE NEVER SHOWED
THIS MORNING -- DISAPPEARED.

38:38.418 --> 38:40.387
OH. WELL,
WHAT ABOUT HIS BODYGUARDS?

38:40.420 --> 38:42.389
WELL, I GUESS
HE'S SMARTER THAN THEY ARE.

38:42.422 --> 38:45.892
OKAY. GONNA KEEP THIS SHORT
AND SWEET, FELLAS AND FELLEES.

38:45.925 --> 38:47.527
THERE ARE CERTAIN CHANGES

38:47.560 --> 38:50.163
THAT WE, AS AN ORGANIZATION,
NEED TO MAKE.

38:50.196 --> 38:53.933
TO THAT END, WE WILL BE
RELEASING SHANE GIVENS,

38:53.967 --> 38:56.503
LLOYD WOODWARD...

38:56.536 --> 39:00.440
BRIAN SEGERMAN, AND...

39:01.541 --> 39:02.542
...AMIR JOHNSON.

39:02.575 --> 39:03.710
[ REPORTERS MURMURING ]

39:03.743 --> 39:07.147
WE WILL ALSO BE PICKING UP
THE OPTION ON TERRENCE KING.

39:07.180 --> 39:10.417
THE BONUS MONEY WE PAY
IS A BARGAIN

39:10.450 --> 39:14.421
TO KEEP THIS BRAVE NATIONAL HERO
IN A HAWKS UNIFORM.

39:14.454 --> 39:16.122
THAT'S WHAT I GOT.
THANK YOU.

39:16.156 --> 39:18.858
[ REPORTERS ASKING QUESTIONS ]

39:18.892 --> 39:21.895
HE CUTS HALF OUR SECONDARY
TO KEEP A PLAYER WHO CAN'T RUN?

39:25.165 --> 39:27.967
DID YOU HAVE
SOMETHING TO DO WITH THIS?

39:28.001 --> 39:30.437
NO. I DIDN'T.

39:31.571 --> 39:32.639
[ SIGHS ]

39:32.672 --> 39:35.975
WELL, LOOK, AT LEAST
WE BOUGHT T.K. SOME TIME, RIGHT?

39:36.009 --> 39:37.444
TRUE.

39:37.477 --> 39:39.479
AS OF NOW, TERRENCE KING
IS STILL A NEW YORK HAWK.

39:39.512 --> 39:43.516
THE QUESTION IS,
WHERE THE HELL IS HE?

39:45.585 --> 39:48.922
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

39:54.928 --> 39:56.463
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

39:56.496 --> 39:58.164
[ RINGING STOPS ]

39:58.198 --> 39:59.466
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

39:59.499 --> 40:02.469
MY BAD ON THE TIME.

40:02.502 --> 40:04.571
HAD TO SHAKE THE GOONS.

40:06.539 --> 40:08.174
YOU COMING, OR WHAT?

40:23.289 --> 40:24.991
I KNOW YOUR GAME.

40:26.226 --> 40:28.695
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

40:28.728 --> 40:30.263
ROOK TO KNIGHT-FOUR?

40:30.296 --> 40:32.132
THE LAYOFFS,
HURTING TEAM MORALE,

40:32.165 --> 40:34.934
PICKING UP T.K.'s BONUS,
DROPPING FOUR OTHER PLAYERS --

40:34.968 --> 40:37.103
IT ALL
DEVALUES THE TEAM.

40:37.137 --> 40:39.572
WHY WOULD I WANT TO LOWER
THE VALUE OF MY OWN BUSINESS?

40:39.606 --> 40:42.208
EVERY DOLLAR LESS
THIS TEAM IS WORTH,

40:42.242 --> 40:44.944
IT'S 50 CENTS
YOU DON'T HAVE TO PAY YOUR WIFE.

40:44.978 --> 40:45.979
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:46.012 --> 40:47.514
FOR PERSONAL VENDETTA,

40:47.547 --> 40:49.582
YOU ARE GOING TO
DESTROY THIS TEAM.

40:49.616 --> 40:51.551
AND ROME BURNED DOWN
AROUND THEM.

40:51.584 --> 40:53.119
YOU REALIZE
THAT THE LEAGUE

40:53.153 --> 40:54.988
WILL NEVER LET YOU
GET AWAY WITH THIS.

40:55.021 --> 40:56.556
MM.

40:56.589 --> 40:59.926
GET AWAY WITH WHAT --
PROTECTING MY CAP SPACE?

40:59.959 --> 41:00.927
HM?

41:00.960 --> 41:01.795
PICKING UP THE CONTRACT

41:01.828 --> 41:03.997
OF AN ALL-STAR
WHO'S LIKELY TO RECOVER?

41:04.030 --> 41:07.967
YOU WORRY TOO MUCH.
GIVES YOU FROWN LINES.

41:08.001 --> 41:11.905
ONCE I REGAIN FULL CONTROL,
I CAN REBUILD THIS TEAM --

41:13.173 --> 41:14.107
WE'LL DO IT TOGETHER.

41:14.140 --> 41:16.276
WE DESTROY THE VILLAGE
IN ORDER TO SAVE IT?

41:16.309 --> 41:17.243
IS THAT THE SPIN?

41:17.277 --> 41:23.016
PROTECTING SOMETHING...
ISN'T ALWAYS SIMPLE.

41:30.190 --> 41:31.324
YES.

41:31.358 --> 41:33.993
DAD KNOWS I'M GROUNDED,
SO YOU KNOW WHERE TO FIND ME.

41:34.027 --> 41:35.528
MM-HMM.

41:37.330 --> 41:39.232
RAY JAY, LISTEN.

41:41.167 --> 41:43.303
YOU WERE RIGHT
ABOUT A FEW THINGS.

41:43.336 --> 41:44.204
WHAT?

41:44.237 --> 41:47.007
WELL, YOU<i>ARE</i>
GONNA BE 18 SOON,

41:47.040 --> 41:50.210
AND I WON'T AGREE
WITH EVERY CHOICE YOU MAKE.

41:50.243 --> 41:52.946
I CAN'T PROTECT YOU
FROM EVERYTHING.

41:52.979 --> 41:55.982
BUT THERE'S ONE THING
I<i>CAN</i>DO,

41:56.016 --> 42:00.286
AND THAT'S
HELP YOU PROTECT<i>YOURSELF.</i>

42:05.291 --> 42:07.260
[ BAG RUSTLES ]

42:09.662 --> 42:11.231
YOU GOT ME CONDOMS.

42:11.264 --> 42:13.199
HOW ABOUT
YOU AND YOUR FATHER

42:13.233 --> 42:16.336
DISCUSS, YOU KNOW...
THE DETAILS?

42:16.369 --> 42:19.372
BUT...DON'T BE AN IDIOT.

42:19.406 --> 42:21.207
USE PROTECTION.

42:21.241 --> 42:22.342
RIGHT.

42:22.375 --> 42:26.980
AND, RAY JAY, LISTEN.
YOU'RE STILL GROUNDED FOR LYING.

42:27.013 --> 42:30.350
AS LONG AS YOU'RE UNDER MY ROOF,
IT'S MY HOUSE, MY RULES.

42:30.383 --> 42:32.252
YEAH.

42:32.285 --> 42:33.987
YEAH?
YEAH.

42:37.057 --> 42:39.826
DUDE, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU GOT ME CONDOMS.

42:39.859 --> 42:41.594
ME NEITHER.

42:43.396 --> 42:45.165
AND I'M NOT YOUR DUDE!

42:45.198 --> 42:47.267
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

42:48.268 --> 42:55.041
* OH, YOU KNOW IT'S THE SOUND
THAT ARRESTS MY SOUL *

42:55.075 --> 42:57.377
I'M YOUR MOTHER.

42:59.446 --> 43:01.648
* THE RHYTHM THAT OUR HEARTS
POUND OUT ROLLS ON *
